CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, October 8, 1960, pg. 16, reads: "Matching Bats - All the talk was about hitting when Bill Mazeroski and Joe Christopher talked shop before the start of the Pittsburgh Pirates' first World Series game in 33 years.  The talk appeared to pay off for the classy Pirate second baseman as he contributed a home and single to the Bucs' win. - Harris Photos."
TitMainTitle: Pittsburgh Pirates baseball players Bill Mazeroski and Joe Christopher standing on field before opening game of 1960 World Series, Forbes Field
